    "text": "Definition: Yellow discoloration of the sclera and skin due to hyperbilirubinaemia.\n• Clinical Jaundice: Bilirubin > 3 mg/dL (50 µmol/L).\n• Latent Jaundice: Bilirubin > 1 mg/dL but < 3 mg/dL."
