            "text": "Courvoisier's Law",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "text": "In a jaundiced patient, a palpable non-tender gallbladder is unlikely to be due to gallstones (usually Ca Head of Pancreas). Rationale: Chronic stones cause fibrosis (shrunken GB)."
